  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Cash Transfer Project for Balaka District</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CA plans to target the people with 2-3 multi-purpose cash intervention, which the beneficiary households will use to buy food and other immediate needs, as they concentrate on the rain fed cultivation CA is implementing in some of the project areas as a way of mitigation against the drought effects. The project will target  about 1,000 beneficiaries. CA plans to use this grant to fund the 2-3 months multi-purpose cash grants, which will help to avert rapidly increasing malnutrition cases and assist households in taking positive coping mechanisms.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project is expected to help households access food and other immediate household needs during the critical months of December, January, February, when they will still be waiting for harvest from the rain fed agriculture. This means the project will assist in providing immediate food and other basic needs which will be measured by changes in number of meals per day and narratives on protection of livelihood assets in the beneficiary households (from using qualitative methodologies).The project is linked to interventions under Health Governance Funded by the Scottish Government in addressing food crisis and reversing the trend in malnutrition cases.</narrative>
  </description>
